<p class="">The right hon. Gentleman should be frank with the House. He is referring to the occasion when Mr. Balfour moved the Closure in 1902. That was after all the Amendments had been disposed of and only to prevent a general discussion on the Schedule.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
